<item>
            <title>[NIFI-9389] ExecuteProcess NullPointerException when not Triggered</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NIFI-9389</link>
                <project id="12316020" key="NIFI">Apache NiFi</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When an &quot;ExecuteProcess&quot; processor is configured to run only on the primary node of a cluster, the &quot;Run Once&quot; and &quot;Stop&quot; commands cause an NPE to be thrown on all non-primary nodes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would also happen on any node if the &quot;Cron&quot; scheduling strategy was used, and the processor was started and stopped without being triggered by the cron expression.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
